<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Would be nice to be able to specify message options with a string too as an alternative to an array.
I found it really useful especially with validator who have only one error message.</p>

<p>So this :</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
if (isset($options['messages']) &amp;&amp; is_array($options['messages'])) {
    $validator-&gt;setMessages($options['messages']);
}
</code></pre>

<p>Could be replace by :</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
if (isset($options['messages']) ) {
    if(is_array($options['messages'])){
        $validator-&gt;setMessages($options['messages']);
    }else{
        $validator-&gt;setMessage($options['messages']);
    }
}
</code></pre>

